The corresponding notification must be sent no later than three months after receipt of the confirmation of receipt of the request.
Upon receipt of the request, the Ministry of Finance will examine whether the request meets all legal requirements.
After that, it will submit the request to the relevant company via the Financial Directorate in question. If the request for recovery is granted, the company will have to determine, among other things, the debtor's assets, for example, by excerpts from the land register, enquiries about existing bank accounts and registration of vehicles with the registration office.
