Germany: there are no regulations at the federal level.
Accordingly, the statistics compiled at the federal level for auditors and UST special auditors do not provide information on particularly "productive" audit fields.
Regarding the analysis of such information, the usefulness and the way in which it will be used, there were different views among the survey points.
Some superfinancial Directorates provide the FÄ with such information, but the FÄ is free to use it or not.
4.5.4 comparison and evaluation
As a result, large amounts of information are processed automatically in the Cz. Among other things, data from Ust audits, as well as key figures from balance sheets, profit and loss statements are processed in the system.
CZ is able to manage the selection of high-risk cases on the basis of a wide range of information.
The same applies to the evaluation and management of UST audits in general.
In the Czech Republic, the establishment of a special tax office for large enterprises is planned for 2012.
In Germany, the financial administration does not collect comparable amounts of data.
It is therefore more difficult to carry out these tasks in the same way.
The emphasis is more on the selection of relevant individual cases.
